<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F63FEED48A754A9FE2BF9F1" pageId="301" pageNumber="302" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F63FEED48A754A9FE00FA2D" blockId="301.[151,1437,901,1718]" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F63FEED48A754A9FE15FC6D" bold="true" box="[151,432,901,926]" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F63FEED4AFC54A9FCF9FC6D" box="[716,860,901,925]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6499999999999995" metricValueMax="8.7" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="301" pageNumber="302" unit="mm" value="6.6499999999999995" valueMax="8.7" valueMin="4.6">4.6–8.7 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible brown and partly testaceous; occasionally anterior margin of clypeus testaceous; antenna brown, except segments 1–2 and occasionally also part of 3 testaceous (in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18F63FEED4B6254E1FC32FC15" box="[850,919,973,997]" name="China" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">China</collectingCountry>
, Mt. Wuyishan, antenna testaceous, except segments 6–10 slightly darkened); mesosoma and metasoma black, except margins of pronotum testaceous; legs testaceous, occasionally with metacoxa, meso- and metaclub of femur, meso- and metatibia partly brown. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 18:6:55:30:22:14:12:10:10:12. Head shiny, strongly reticulate rugose mainly on face; vertex with numerous strong longitudinal keels; frontal line complete; occipital carina complete; posterior ocelli not touching occipital carina; POL = 4; OL = 4; OOL = 11; in small specimen (
<quantity id="C731ABA48F63FEED48AE5389FEA0FB4D" box="[158,261,1189,1213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="301" pageNumber="302" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.60 mm</quantity>
) from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18F63FEED49625389FE3DFB4D" box="[338,408,1189,1213]" name="China" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">China</collectingCountry>
, Mt. Wuyishan, POL = 2; OL = 4; OOL = 11. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F63FEED4C115389FB34FB4D" box="[1057,1169,1189,1213]" captionStart="PLATE 86" captionStartId="302.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[203,1376,241,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-79@302.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="302" captionText="PLATE 86. A, D. Pronotum in lateral view, holotypes. B, C, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Dryinus barbarus. B. D. asiaticus. C. D. barbarus. D. D. orientalis. E. D. gibbosoides. Scale bar 1.24 mm for A, 0.16 mm for B, 0.36 mm for C, 1.53 mm for D and 0.22 mm for E. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278682/files/figure.png" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">Plate 86A</figureCitation>
) shiny, smooth, weakly granulated or unsculptured, with some areolae near posterior margin; disc humped; pronotal tubercle not reaching tegula. Scutum reticulate rugose, with surface near anterior margin smooth and unsculptured. Notauli absent. Scutellum and metanotum completely reticulate rugose. Propodeum reticulate rugose; posterior surface with two longitudinal keels. Fore wing with one dark transverse band; distal part of stigmal vein about as long as proximal part. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 18:3:6:13:26. Enlarged claw spatulate (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F63FEED4C875275FA8FFA81" box="[1207,1322,1369,1393]" captionStart="PLATE 86" captionStartId="302.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[203,1376,241,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-79@302.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="302" captionText="PLATE 86. A, D. Pronotum in lateral view, holotypes. B, C, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Dryinus barbarus. B. D. asiaticus. C. D. barbarus. D. D. orientalis. E. D. gibbosoides. Scale bar 1.24 mm for A, 0.16 mm for B, 0.36 mm for C, 1.53 mm for D and 0.22 mm for E. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278682/files/figure.png" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">Plate 86C</figureCitation>
), without subapical tooth, with some bristles and three–four distal lamellae. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F63FEED4C965251FAB3FA65" box="[1190,1302,1405,1429]" captionStart="PLATE 86" captionStartId="302.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[203,1376,241,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-79@302.[166,1421,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="302" captionText="PLATE 86. A, D. Pronotum in lateral view, holotypes. B, C, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Dryinus barbarus. B. D. asiaticus. C. D. barbarus. D. D. orientalis. E. D. gibbosoides. Scale bar 1.24 mm for A, 0.16 mm for B, 0.36 mm for C, 1.53 mm for D and 0.22 mm for E. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278682" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278682/files/figure.png" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">Plate 86C</figureCitation>
) with inner margin straight, without distal prominence, with two rows of about 32–38 lamellae extending continuously to distal apex. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F63FEED48F752C5FE2BF9F1" blockId="301.[151,1437,901,1718]" box="[199,398,1513,1537]" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F63FEED48F752C5FEAEF9F1" bold="true" box="[199,267,1513,1537]" pageId="301" pageNumber="302">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
